---
import DocsLayout from '../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import {docsHomeCards} from '../lib/docs';
---

<DocsLayout
  title="CommerceForge Docs"
  description="Installation, deployment, B2B, i18n, and theming guides for CommerceForge."
>
  <p class="mb-3 text-[11px] font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.28em] text-zinc-500">Documentation</p>
  <h1 class="mt-0 max-w-[10ch] text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-50 md:text-6xl">
    Production docs for CommerceForge.
  </h1>
  <p class="lead mt-6">
    CommerceForge is a production-ready Shopify Hydrogen storefront starter for agencies and
    developers. This documentation covers setup, environment variables, B2B, internationalization,
    theming, and deployment.
  </p>

  <div class="docs-grid">
    <div class="docs-panel">
      <h3 class="text-base font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-50">B2C + B2B</h3>
      <p>
        One codebase for consumer storefronts and Shopify Plus B2B flows.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="docs-panel">
      <h3 class="text-base font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-50">27 locales</h3>
      <p>
        Markets-aware localization with RTL support and path-prefix routing.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="docs-panel">
      <h3 class="text-base font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-50">Release-ready</h3>
      <p>
        Local development, Oxygen deployment, and commercial release packaging.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <blockquote>
    <p>
      Start with installation, then configure environment variables, connect Shopify, and move into
      B2B, localization, theming, and deployment once the storefront is running locally.
    </p>
  </blockquote>

  <h2>Start here</h2>
  <div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
    {docsHomeCards.map((card) => (
      <a
        class="group border border-zinc-800/80 bg-zinc-900/25 p-5 transition hover:border-zinc-700 hover:bg-zinc-900/45"
        href={card.href}
      >
        <p class="mb-2 text-[11px] font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.24em] text-zinc-500">
          Guide
        </p>
        <h3 class="m-0 text-lg font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-50">{card.label}</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 mb-0 text-sm leading-7 text-zinc-400">{card.description}</p>
      </a>
    ))}
  </div>

  <h2>What’s inside CommerceForge</h2>
  <p>
    The storefront ships with collections, products, variants, cart, checkout, predictive search,
    full-page search, blogs, customer accounts, B2B pricing via buyer context, request-a-quote,
    Shopify Markets localization, RTL support, and a responsive UI system built with shadcn/ui and
    Tailwind CSS.
  </p>

  <p>
    Use the guides on the left to set up your environment, connect Shopify, configure B2B, deploy
    to Oxygen, and customize the design system.
  </p>
</DocsLayout>
